Canny Maphanga Suspects open fire on police officers (Supplied) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Two police officers were rushed to hospital after the suspects they were tailing opened fire. The officers were said to have been trailing a Toyota on Main Reef Road in Langlaagte, Johannesburg, on Thursday. Suspects in the Toyota allegedly opened fire when the vehicle made a slight turn and the two officers passed them. A bullet grazed the head of one officer while another was shot in the shoulder. Gauteng police spokesperson Captain Kay Makhubele was not immediately available for comment.    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.